    <p>{`On the webpage under `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://guides.rubyonrails.org/routing.html#using-root"
      }}>{`#using-root`}</a>{`, it informs us that you can specify where `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`/`}</inlineCode>{` should route to with the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`root`}</inlineCode>{` method.`}</p>
    <p>{`We can do this with `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`root to: 'controller_name#action_name`}</inlineCode>{` which in shorthand is `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`root 'controller_name#action_name'`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
    <p>{`And so, we update the page like so:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-rb"
      }}>{`Rails.application.routes.draw do
  # For details on the DSL available within this file, see https://guides.rubyonrails.org/routing.html
  root "application#hello"
end
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`For future reference, you can also specify a root within a `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`namespace`}</inlineCode>{` like so:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-rb"
